{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"desirous-judicial-hogget","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Let Dockerfile.reviewbot's entrypoint materialize the persistent tickets worktree (git clone --single-branch of the tickets branch) with REVIEWBOT_TICKETS_PAT set.\n2. Any store WRITE from the container (emit_code_review_artifact -> rebar.create_ticket, repo_root=None -> tracker /var/gerrit/site/reviewbot-tickets) fails: first with 'ticket system not initialized' (.env-id is GITIGNORED so no clone ever has it; only rebar init / the ensure-registry generates it), and after ensures with 'Author identity unknown' (container has no git user.name/email).\n3. emit_code_review_artifact swallows the exception (best-effort by design), so every prod review silently emits nothing — the code_review data-capture feature (story limestone-unethical-zebrafinch) has never produced a real artifact (the only code_review tickets in the store are test fixtures).\n\n**Expected:** a fresh container + volume yields a writable ambient store; artifacts are emitted+pushed per review. **Actual:** write-dead store; silent no-op emission.\n\nProven on prod 2026-07-10 (f600 verification): in-container probe reproduced both failures; after run_ensures(tracker) + repo-local git identity (RebarBotNava / joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com) a probe create succeeded AND auto-pushed to origin/tickets (d3ee-c7b6-061e-4a66). The prod worktree volume is now manually converged, but any FRESH volume/clone regresses — the entrypoint must do this.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Entrypoint (or app startup) runs the ensure-registry (rebar._store.ensures.run_ensures) and sets a repo-local git identity on the tickets worktree after clone — idempotent on restart.\n- [ ] A container test (or stub harness) proves a write against a fresh single-branch clone succeeds.\n- [ ] Emission failures are observable: the swallowed exception should at least surface in a countable log marker (observability greppable), not only DEBUG.\n- [ ] File paths: infra/compose/Dockerfile.reviewbot, src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py.","id":"d220-eeda-1909-4147","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"review-bot entrypoint's fresh tickets clone is write-dead: no .env-id ensure, no git identity — artifact emission structurally broken"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783717233835053001,"uuid":"725654c7-b368-4354-9889-d988775864ac"}